article.description: — Bryce Workman had a season-high 25 points as Jacksonville stretched its home winning streak to 11 games, beating Eastern Kentucky 81-68 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Workman carries Jacksonville over E. Kentucky 81-68
article.linkText: Workman carries Jacksonville over E. Kentucky 81-68
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- — Bryce Workman had a season-high 25 points as Jacksonville stretched its home winning streak to 11 games, beating Eastern Kentucky 81-68 on Wednesday night. Workman made 11 of 14 shots. He added nine rebounds. Kevion Nolan had 15 points for Jacksonville (15-8, 7-4 Atlantic Sun Conference). Mike Marsh added 12 points and seven rebounds. Jordan Davis had 11 points. Tyreese Davis had 10 points and 10 rebounds. Cooper Robb had 14 points for the Colonels (11-14, 3-8). Curt Lewis also scored 14 points and had nine rebounds. Russhard Cruickshank had 11 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
